news.title: Godrej Properties buys two group housing plots in Gurugram for Rs 515 crore
news.para: The land parcels together will offer a development potential of over 1 million sq ft and an estimated revenue potential of over Rs 3,400 crore.

news.title: Goa to extend automated building plan approval to multi-dwelling units
news.para: The BPAMS is designed to analyse building plans within minutes to check if the construction plans adhere to TCP’s planning rules and guidelines. The system generates a set of reports which specify if the construction plan has violated the Goa Land Development and Building Construction Regulations.

news.title: Noida authority plans to increase FAR for industrial land and townships
news.para: The new regulations will allow a general FAR of 1.5 and a purchasable FAR of 1 — totalling 2.5 — on industrial plots located off roads that are at least 24 metres wide in existing hubs.

news.title: Unitech restarts construction of South Park project in Gurugram
news.para: The project, which was halted in 2013, is now set to move forward and be completed within the next three years. The South Park project originally aimed to deliver 832 flats spread across 27.4 acres, but only 672 units were sold before the project was stalled.

news.title: Raymond's chairman expects its real estate vertical to be listed by August 2025
news.para: Singhania expects its real estate vertical to be listed by July or August next year and each of the three listed verticals will be governed by their independent board and chart their growth strategies.

news.title: Bombay HC rejects pre-arrest bail to builder in case of 'duping; doctor of Rs 90 lakh
news.para: "An innocent and unsuspecting investor has been made to run from pillar to post for over a period of 10 years. What exacerbates the situation is the utterly dishonest stand of the applicant," said Justice N J Jamadar on Aug 26.

news.title: PVR INOX plans monetisation of real estate assets
news.para: Now, PVR INOX will partner with developers to jointly invest in new screen capex by shifting towards a franchise-owned and company-operated (FOCO) model.

news.title: NBCC announces issue of bonus shares in 1:2 ratio
news.para: "The Board of Directors has recommended the issuance of bonus shares to the shareholders of the company in the ratio of 1:2 i.e. one new fully paid-up equity share of Rs 1 each for every two existing shares to the eligible members as on the record Date," the company said.

news.title: Dharavi NGOs support redevelopment survey, say opposition only by non-locals
news.para: ​The NGOs have written to Dharavi Redevelopment Project/Slum Rehabilitation Authority (DRP/SRA), a government of Maharashtra body overseeing the USD 3-billion redevelopment project being executed by the Adani group, extending support for the survey.

news.title: Registration of properties in Mumbai region set to rise 7% in August 2024: Knight Frank
news.para: ​Citing Maharashtra government data, real estate consultant Knight Frank India said that Mumbai city (area under BMC jurisdiction) has recorded 11,631 property registrations so far in the month of August.

news.title: Bajaj Housing Finance Rs 6,560-crore IPO to open on September 9
news.para: The proposed IPO comprises a fresh issue of equity shares of up to Rs 3,560 crore and an offer for sale (OFS) of equity shares to the tune of Rs 3,000 crore by parent Bajaj Finance.

news.title: Noida: 60% stalled projects avail Uttar Pradesh's rehabilitation package
news.para: At a review meeting with chief minister Yogi Adityanath on Aug 24, the three authorities reported that 93 out of 161 projects have already availed of the package, which was announced by the govt in Dec last year.

news.title: Hyderabad: 1,100 buildings found in FTL, buffer zones of 13 lakes
news.para: Among the 1,100 structures, 462 are in FTL and 634 in buffer zones of the lakes, revenue authorities claimed. A majority of these illegal structures have come up in and around 13 lakes in the two districts.

news.title: Birla Estates to co-develop 131 acres land in Noida sector 150
news.para: In July 2024, the company acquired five acre land in sector 71, Gurugram with a development potential of around 10 lakh sq ft. This is expected to generate revenue of over Rs 1,400 crore.

news.title: NBCC sells office spaces worth Rs 14,800 crore in Delhi
news.para: Through this e-auction, out of the total area sold, around 1.21 lakh sq ft having sale value of approximately Rs 596.25 crore has been sold to PSU/government entities and 0.60 lakh sq ft having sale value of Rs 312.23 crore was sold to private entities.

news.title: Greater Noida authority offers 22 commercial plots
news.para: Registrations for these commercial plots began on August 29 and will remain open until September 19, 2024, according to Greater Noida authority.

news.title: NeoLiv and Royal Green Realty to develop 20-acre township in Sonipat
news.para: The gross development value of the project is over Rs 600 crore and will offer villas, independent floors and plots.

news.title: Goa govt to seek fresh environmental clearances for traditional sand mining permits
news.para: The process will be completed within the next four months, advocate general Devidas Pangam said, adding that govt will focus on expediting the matter.

news.title: Andhra Pradesh government orders district command centers to oversee sand sales
news.para: A new sand policy comes into effect from September 11, ensuring transparency with measures like online booking and daily stock updates for public awareness.

news.title: EOW Mumbai files FIR against four for mortgaging flat twice
news.para: All the accused, who are in the construction business, are relatives and stay at Malabar Hill.
